---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import CTABar from '../components/CTABar.astro';
import business from '../data/business.json';

const pageURL = new URL(Astro.url.pathname, Astro.site).toString();
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Snyder's Outdoor Solutions"
  description="How Snyder's Outdoor Solutions collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
  canonical={pageURL}
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="bg-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand-light text-brand-dark ring-1 ring-brand/20 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-brand"></span>
        Legal
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-gray-900 text-3xl md:text-5xl mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: this document is draft boilerplate pending legal review.</p>
      <Prose>
        <p>
          Snyder's Outdoor Solutions ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy. This policy describes what
          information we collect when you interact with our website and services, how we use it, and the choices
          you have. Because this is draft boilerplate for a small local service business, you should review it
          with counsel before treating it as your final policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>We collect information in two primary ways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Information you give us.</strong> When you request an estimate, call us, or submit a form,
            we collect your name, phone number, email (if provided), property address or location, and the details
            of your service request.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> When you browse our site, we collect standard
            analytics information via Google Analytics (through Google Tag Manager) — page views, device type,
            approximate location based on IP, referral source, and interaction events. We also use Microsoft
            Clarity to record anonymous session data (heatmaps and interaction patterns) to improve the site.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to your service request, schedule work, and deliver the services you ask for.</li>
          <li>To communicate with you about your estimate, appointment, or invoice.</li>
          <li>To improve our website, our marketing, and the way we communicate with prospective customers.</li>
          <li>To comply with applicable laws and protect our legal rights.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. We share information only with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Service providers we rely on</strong> — for example, our scheduling software (Jobber), our
            analytics provider (Google), and our session-analytics provider (Microsoft Clarity). These providers
            are bound by their own privacy obligations and use the data only to provide their services to us.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal and regulatory</strong> — if required by law, court order, or legitimate legal process.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our site uses cookies and similar technologies for analytics and tag management purposes. You can disable
          cookies in your browser settings; some site functionality may be limited as a result.
        </p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep contact and job information for as long as needed to provide and support our services and to
          comply with applicable legal obligations. Analytics data is retained according to each provider's
          default retention settings.
        </p>

        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>
          You can request a copy of the personal information we have about you, ask us to correct it, or ask us
          to delete it, by contacting us using the details below. Some information may be retained if we're
          required to keep it by law.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are directed to adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children
          under 13.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we'll revise the "last updated" date at the
          top. Material changes may also be announced on the site itself.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy can go to <a href="/contact">our contact page</a> or directly to {business.name}
          at the phone number listed in our site footer.
        </p>
      </Prose>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABar />
</BaseLayout>
